nodes.name: Control Assessor
nodes.description: Individual or group responsible for conducting a comprehensive assessment of the management, operational, and technical controls.

nodes.name: Common Control Provider
nodes.description: Individual or group responsible for the development, implementation, assessment, and monitoring of common controls.

nodes.name: System Owner
nodes.description: Official responsible for the procurement, development, integration, modification, operation, maintenance, and disposal of an information system.

nodes.name: Senior Information Security Officer
nodes.description: Official responsible for serving as the primary liaison between the organization’s authorizing officials, information system owners, and common control providers.

nodes.name: Chief Information Officer
nodes.description: Official responsible for the organization’s information management functions.

nodes.name: Authorizing Official
nodes.description: Senior official with the authority to formally assume responsibility for operating an information system at an acceptable level of risk.

nodes.name: Monitor
nodes.description: Monitor the system and the associated controls on an ongoing basis to include assessing control effectiveness and documenting changes.

nodes.name: Authorize
nodes.description: Authorize the system or common controls based on a determination that the risk to organizational operations and assets is acceptable.

nodes.name: Select
nodes.description: Select an initial set of controls for the system and tailor the controls as needed to reduce risk to an acceptable level.

nodes.name: Categorize
nodes.description: Categorize the system and the information processed

nodes.name: Supply Chain Risk Management
nodes.description: Controls that address the risks associated with the supply chain.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a supply chain risk management policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the supply chain risk management policy.

nodes.name: System and Information Integrity
nodes.description: Controls that ensure the integrity of the information system and the information it processes.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a system and information integrity policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the system and information integrity policy.

nodes.name: System and Communications Protection
nodes.description: Controls that ensure the security of the information system's communications and the protection of information at rest and in transit.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a system and communications protection policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the system and communications protection policy.

nodes.name: System and Services Acquisition
nodes.description: Controls that address the acquisition of products and services and the development of information systems.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a system and services acquisition policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the system and services acquisition policy.

nodes.name: Risk Assessment
nodes.description: Controls that address the organization's risk assessment policy and procedures.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a risk assessment policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the risk assessment policy.

nodes.name: PII Processing and Transparency
nodes.description: Controls that address privacy risks to individuals resulting from the processing of personally identifiable information (PII).

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a PII processing and transparency policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the PII processing and transparency policy.

nodes.name: Personnel Security
nodes.description: Controls that ensure individuals occupying positions of responsibility within organizations are trustworthy and meet established security criteria.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a personnel security policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the personnel security policy.

nodes.name: Program Management
nodes.description: Controls that address the organization's information security program.

nodes.name: Information Security Program Plan
nodes.description: The organization develops and disseminates an organization-wide information security program plan.

nodes.name: Planning
nodes.description: Controls that address the security planning for organizational information systems.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a security planning policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the security planning policy.

nodes.name: Physical and Environmental Protection
nodes.description: Controls that address the physical security of the facility and the environmental controls (e.g., temperature, humidity, power).

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a physical and environmental protection policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the physical and environmental protection policy.

nodes.name: Media Protection
nodes.description: Controls that protect information system media (both digital and non-digital).

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a media protection policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the media protection policy.

nodes.name: Maintenance
nodes.description: Controls that describe the requirements for maintaining information systems and the tools used for such maintenance.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a system maintenance policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the system maintenance policy.

nodes.name: Incident Response
nodes.description: Controls that address the organization's incident handling capabilities for security incidents.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) an incident response policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the incident response policy.

nodes.name: Identification and Authentication
nodes.description: Controls that ensure the information system uniquely identifies and authenticates organizational users (or processes acting on behalf of organizational users).

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) an identification and authentication policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the identification and authentication policy.

nodes.name: Contingency Planning
nodes.description: Controls that address the plans and procedures for recovering information systems and operations after a disruption.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a contingency planning policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the contingency planning policy.

nodes.name: Configuration Management
nodes.description: Controls that establish and maintain the integrity of information system products and systems through control of the processes for initializing, changing, and monitoring the configurations of those products and systems.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a configuration management policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the configuration management policy.

nodes.name: Assessment, Authorization, and Monitoring
nodes.description: Controls that ensure organizational officials perform periodic security assessments and authorization actions, and implement continuous monitoring.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a security assessment and authorization policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the security assessment and authorization policy.

nodes.name: Audit and Accountability
nodes.description: Controls that support the organization’s ability to generate, process, protect, and review audit records.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) an audit and accountability policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the audit and accountability policy.

nodes.name: Awareness and Training
nodes.description: Controls that ensure managers and users of information systems are made aware of the security risks associated with their activities and of the applicable laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, standards, instructions, regulations, or procedures related to the security of organizational information systems.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) a security awareness and training policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the security awareness and training policy.

nodes.name: Access Control
nodes.description: Controls that limit access to information systems and information to authorized users, processes, and devices.

nodes.name: Policy and Procedures
nodes.description: The organization develops, documents, and disseminates to defined personnel or roles: (a) an access control policy; and (b) procedures to facilitate the implementation of the access control policy and associated access controls.

nodes.name: Assess
nodes.description: Assess the controls to determine if the controls are implemented correctly

nodes.name: Implement
nodes.description: Implement the controls and describe how the controls are employed within the system and its environment of operation.

nodes.name: Prepare
nodes.description: Carry out essential activities to help prepare the organization to manage its security and privacy risks using the Risk Management Framework.
